# Ansible Galaxy dependency maintenance

When `requirements.yml` (or related dependency work) is in context, offer or run a version check if it has not been done recently.

## What to compare

**Collections** (listed in `requirements.yml`; mostly unpinned):

- `ansible.posix`, `community.crypto`, `community.docker`, `community.general`, `community.windows`, `vladgh.samba`, `artis3n.tailscale`
- Installed: `ansible-galaxy collection list`
- Latest: Ansible Galaxy API (`highest_version` per collection)

**Pinned roles**:

- `geerlingguy.docker` (pinned `7.4.7`) — also check GitHub tags on `geerlingguy/ansible-role-docker`
- `geerlingguy.nfs` (pinned `2.1.0`) — GitHub tags on `geerlingguy/ansible-role-nfs`

## Upgrade cautions

Treat as higher risk (test before bumping pins):

- `community.general` major versions (e.g. 12.x → 13.x)
- `geerlingguy.docker` major versions (e.g. 7.x → 8.x)

User-local collections live under `~/.ansible/collections/`; system packages may come from the distro `ansible` package.

## Suggested cadence

Roughly quarterly, or when touching `requirements.yml`, `nas.yml` requirements roles, or after Ansible/ansible-nas upgrades.

## Commands

```bash
ansible-galaxy collection list
ansible-galaxy role list
cd /mnt/nas/media/code/ansible-nas && ansible-galaxy collection install -r requirements.yml --upgrade  # user-local only
```
